item.title: Boarding up UK Churchill statue ‘shameful’
item.description: British Prime Minister Boris Johnson says it's "absurd and shameful" that the statue of Winston Churchill in Parliament Square, London, is at risk of attack from anti-racism protesters.

item.title: Bomb explodes in Kabul mosque, 4 dead
item.description: A bomb has exploded inside a mosque in west Kabul killing at least four people, including the prayer leader, and wounding an unknown number of others, an Afghan government official says.

item.title: Philippine protest slams anti-terror bill
item.description: More than 1000 Filipinos have braved the threat of coronavirus infection to protest against a controversial new anti-terrorism bill, which is awaiting Philippine President Rodrigo Duterte's signature.

item.title: Airlines in legal fight over UK quarantine
item.description: British Airways, easyJet and Ryanair have begun legal action against the British government's quarantine policy in a bid to overturn what they see as overly strict rules.

item.title: Latest snapshot of the coronavirus impact
French police protest over chokehold ban
item.description: Police have staged protests in cities across France against a ban on chokehold restraint techniques imposed by the government in response to public anger over the death of George Floyd and alleged police brutality in France.

item.title: UK economy shrank by 25% in March-April
item.description: Britain's economy shrank by a quarter in the March-April period as entire sectors were shuttered by the coronavirus lockdown, reaching what looks likely to be the bottom of a "catastrophic" crash before a long and slow recovery.

item.title: Two key NT national parks to reopen
item.description: The Northern Territory's Kakadu and Uluru-Kata Tjuta national parks will reopen next week amid the easing of coronavirus restrictions.

item.title: Melbourne warehouse roof collapses
item.description: The roof of a vacant warehouse in Melbourne's north has collapsed, with more than 20 firefighters on the scene.

item.title: Global shares, oil slump amid virus fears
item.description: A slump in global shares has extended to its fourth day running and oil has tumbled over growing concerns a resurgence of coronavirus infections could stunt the pace of recovery from lockdowns.
